This paper deals with the construction of distance oracles and spanners for graphs with labeled vertices, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents several results and constructions for this problem, which involve data structures, algorithms, and analysis of their properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.CG (computational geometry), which are all relevant to graph theory and algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the stretch-size tradeoff of the constructions, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and optimization, suggesting the sub-categories cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.LG (machine learning) as possible choices as well.
